        output='Based on the provided excerpts from the SpaceX S-1 filing, here is a detailed summary of how the company handles common-control recast accounting, its basis of presentation, and the retrospective recasting of historical periods to include xAI and X Holdings.\n\n### 1. Basis of Presentation & Cautionary Preamble\n*   **U.S. GAAP Compliance:** The consolidated financial statements are prepared in accordance with U.S. Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP), which requires management to make estimates and assumptions (e.g., revenue recognition, tax valuation allowances, inventory reserves, and fair value of intangibles).\n*   **Cautionary Warning:** The preamble explicitly cautions that the summary historical consolidated financial and operating data **is not indicative of expected future results**, nor are interim results necessarily indicative of full fiscal year outcomes. \n*   **Directives to Readers:** The summary data is not intended to replace the full financial statements. Readers are directed to review this data in conjunction with the **"Management’s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations" (MD&A)** and the audited consolidated financial statements and related notes included elsewhere in the prospectus.\n\n### 2. Common-Control Recast Accounting\nThe filing details a series of mergers: xAI\'s acquisition of X Holdings and X.AI Corp. (effective March 28, 2025), followed by SpaceX\'s acquisition of xAI (effective February 2, 2026). \n*   **Common Control Rationale:** These transactions are accounted for as reorganizations of entities under **common control** because Elon Musk held a controlling financial interest and majority voting interest in SpaceX, xAI, and X throughout the periods presented.\n*   **Accounting Mechanics:**\n    *   **Historical Carrying Amounts:** The net assets of the entities are combined retrospectively at their historical carrying amounts.\n    *   **No New Goodwill:** No new goodwill or other intangible assets are recorded as a result of these mergers.\n    *   **Eliminations:** All historical related-party and intercompany transactions between the entities are eliminated in consolidation.\n    *   **Change in Reporting Entity:** This retrospective combination constitutes a formal "change in reporting entity."\n    *   **No Separate Financials:** Because the consolidated financial statements already reflect the reorganization for all periods presented, separate financial statements for xAI and X are not provided.\n\n### 3. Recasting Historical Periods for xAI and X Holdings\nTo present a unified financial picture, historical periods have been heavily recast to reflect the mergers and subsequent corporate actions:\n\n*   **Retroactive Share Conversions:** Historical common shares of X, X.AI Corp., and xAI are presented in the financial statements **as if they had been converted into SpaceX Common Stock** at the applicable exchange rates for all periods presented. \n    *   *X Merger Ratios:* X Holdings common stock converted to xAI common stock at a 2.776 ratio.\n    *   *xAI Merger Ratios:* xAI common stock converted to SpaceX common stock at a 0.1433 ratio (on a pre-split basis).\n*   **Shareholders\' Equity Continuation:** The historical capital stock and shareholders’ equity reflect a continuation of SpaceX’s historical equity, combined with the historical equity of X and xAI, adjusted by the respective merger exchange ratios.\n*   **Exception for xAI Preferred Stock:** Unlike common stock, xAI’s historical Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock is **not retrospectively recast** on an as-converted basis. Because it was a legally distinct equity class prior to the merger, historical balance sheets continue to reflect it as outstanding preferred stock. Its conversion into SpaceX Common Stock is only recognized prospectively in the period the merger actually closed (Q1 2026).\n*   **2026 Stock Split Adjustment:** On May 4, 2026, SpaceX executed a 5-for-1 forward stock split for its Class A, B, and C Common Stock. All historical share and per-share information, as well as the conversion rates of Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock, have been **retroactively adjusted** to reflect this split across all periods presented in the prospectus.',
